The paper discusses Bayesian reinforcement learning algorithms, which involve decision-making and probabilistic modeling. This falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also involves modeling and estimation of Markov decision processes (MDPs), which falls under the category of discrete mathematics (cs.DM) and systems and control (cs.SY). Finally, the paper discusses value functions, which are commonly used in optimization and mathematical programming, falling under the category of mathematical optimization (cs.MA).
